@NTAWolf The tests use Python `unittest` and `unittest.mock`. Writing tests of `get_as_dataframe` are easier, because the incoming cell feed from gspread is always the same, and it's the pandas parser that does all the filtering and transforms. So a single static `cell_feed.xml` file is sufficient to drive the mock Worksheet for all those tests.

Tests for `set_with_dataframe` are more difficult, because each different argument value to the function causes a change in the expected cell feed sent to Google API. Since this bug was an obvious typo, I'm OK with not adding any test coverage along with the fix.

