@uniquegodwin @sebcagnon You can detect the reconnect event either directly or in a namespace. Please see `test_reconnect` and `test_reconnect_with_namespace` for examples. https://github.com/invisibleroads/socketIO-client/blob/master/socketIO_client/tests/__init__.py#L52

    # Directly
    socket.on('connect', on_connect)
    socket.on('disconnect', on_disconnect)
    socket.on('reconnect', on_reconnect)

    # Using namespace
    class Namespace(BaseNamespace):

        def on_connect(self):
            print('[Connected]')

        def on_reconnect(self):
            print('[Reconnected]')

        def on_disconnect(self):
            print('[Disconnected]')

Callbacks defined directly take precedence over callbacks defined in the namespace.

