@mindojo-victor I don't know anything about pycharm, but that seems like a bug in pycharm more than in dateutil. I really, really don't think we should try and rename the package, it would be a ton of pointless work for all downstream users.

I'm somewhat sympathetic to the idea of squatting on the `dateutil` package and just posting a package there that fails with an error saying, "Hey, the package is called python-dateutil!"

Theoretically, we could host a mirror at `dateutil`, but that would needlessly complicate the package management, and then it could be a mess if we forget to update one or the other package and a quarter of people are using `dateutil` instead of `python-dateutil` you'll get weird and inconsistent behaviors.

The workaround for now is putting the following code at `.../templates/admin/base_site.html`:

```
{% extends "admin/base_site.html" %}

{% block extrahead %}
<script>window.CKEDITOR_BASEPATH = '/static/ckeditor/ckeditor/';</script>
{{ block.super }}
{% endblock %}
```

I'm still thinking about a better way, but for now that works.

